# Add Vector Embeddings to the Observations Collection

## Question

The `observations` Typesense collection (shipped 2026-07-12) is lexical-only —
no embedding field, so recall is keyword FTS, not semantic. Add a Typesense
auto-embedding field over gist + observations + decisions and switch
`joelclaw sessions search` to hybrid (keyword + vector) queries.

Candidate embedder: `qwen3-embedding:8b` already pulled in flagg's ollama
(openai-compatible endpoint :11434/v1) via Typesense remote-embedding
model_config; fallback is a Typesense built-in S-BERT model. Constraints:
files stay truth (embedding is projection state, regenerated on --rebuild);
indexing stays idempotent; no paid APIs. Receipts: a semantic query that
lexical search misses ("what did we decide about memory compression" finding
the node-cluster/reflector observation) returning the right page.

## Superseded (2026-07-13)

qmd adopted as the knowledge projection (see evaluate-qmd-brain-recall Resolution) — hybrid semantic recall over the full svx corpus including observations, local models, MCP. Typesense embedding work not needed.
